[[File:PE-mapa-Ibirajuba.png|thumb|right|250px|Location of Ibirajuba within Pernambuco.]] '''Ibirajuba''' is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. Located at 182&nbsp;km away from [[Recife]], capital of the state of Pernambuco. Has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 7.833 inhabitants.
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[Altinho, Pernambuco|Altinho]] and [[Cachoeirinha, Pernambuco|Cachoeirinha]] ('''N'''); [[Lajedo, Pernambuco|Lajedo]] ('''S''' and '''W'''); [[Panelas]] and [[Jurema, Pernambuco|Jurema]] ('''E'''). * Area - 189.59&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 612 m * Hydrography - [[Una River (Pernambuco)|Una River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[Hipoxer√≥fila]] * Climate - Transition between [[tropical]] (Hot and humid) and, [[semi arid]] hot * Annual average temperature - 22.0 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 182&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Ibirajuba''' are based in commerce and [[agribusiness]], especially [[maize|corn]], [[beans]]; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]], [[sheep]], [[pigs]], [[goats]] and [[poultry]].
